reviewText:
I figure at the price I paid --- I should have bought five --- it was a quarter a cartoon... I bought enough of the AMAZON WAREHOUSE
DEALS to get free postage, too.

Great stocking-stuffer at THAT price, eh?

Includes "Bartholomew Versus the Wheel" (1964), "A Haunting We Will Go" (1966), "Snow Excuse" (1966) and "The Chocolate Chase" (1980) all on one DVD. All the cartoons were previously released on DVD except "Snow Excuse."
